cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with network centrality analysis. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) as it mentions the use of clustering algorithms. Additionally, it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with network topology. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it mentions data-driven clustering. Finally, it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with the roles of different nodes within a network.
